{"lemma":"دُبَّة","slug":"دُبَّة","root":"د.ب.ب","root_slug":"د-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11949","n11950","n11951"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to creep, to crawl"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to proceed, to advance, to move slowly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to go on all fours"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to enter"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to steal, to creep"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to spread, to fill, to pervade, to invade"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gain ground"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bear","examples":[{"text":"(astronomy) الدُّبّ الْأَصْغَر (ad-dubb al-ʔaṣḡar, “Ursa Minor”)"},{"text":"(astronomy) الدُّبّ الْأَكْبَر (ad-dubb al-ʔakbar, “Ursa Major”)"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of دَبَّ (dabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"walking along slowly"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"creeping, crawling"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"slow walk"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"creeping, crawling"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *dubb- (“bear”), from Proto-Afroasiatic *dab- (“big animal”). Compare Aramaic דבא (debbā), Hebrew דוב (dov) and Akkadian dabûm."},"ipa":["/dab.ba/","/dubb/","/dabb/","/dibb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11949","headword_ar":"دَبَّةٌ","root":"db","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single act"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of creeping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crawling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walking, leisurely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dibaAbN","text_ar":"دِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gibbous hill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyb","text_ar":"كَثِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, T, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and (in some copies of the K “ or ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tract of red sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an even tract of sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or, as in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an even tract of land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place abounding in sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L:) pl. as above. (TA.) Hence the prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa fulaAnN","text_ar":"وَقَعَ فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY dab~apF mina Alr~amoli","text_ar":"فِى دَبَّةً مِنَ الرَّمْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one fell into,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, a place abounding in sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misfortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the camel in such a place suffers fatigue. (T.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain thing for oil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ointment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a receptacle for seeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bizor","text_ar":"بِزْر"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and olive-oil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) pl. as above. (Sb, M.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of bottle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baT~apN","text_ar":"بَطَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) peculiarly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of glass."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [Form the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dab~aho","text_ar":"دَبَّهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dub~aA='N","text_ar":"دُبَّا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A4-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dababN","text_ar":"دَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":["IAar","T","S","M","K","TA","L"]},{"entry_id":"n11950","headword_ar":"دُبَّةٌ","root":"db","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a way, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, S, M, A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dub~N","text_ar":"دُبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, K,) in both these senses: (M:) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a natural disposition, temper, quality,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibotu dub~atahu","text_ar":"رَكِبْتُ دُبَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dub~ahu","text_ar":"دُبَّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I kept to his state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his way, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did as he did."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEoniY wadub~atiY","text_ar":"دَعْنِى وَدُبَّتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leave thou me and my way, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my natural disposition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (S.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","IAar","T","A","S"]},{"entry_id":"n11951","headword_ar":"دِبَّةٌ","root":"db","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of creeping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crawling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"walking, leisurely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K. *) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa xafiY~u Ald~ib~api","text_ar":"هُوَ خَفِىُّ الدِّبَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stealthy, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of creeping along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (M, K:) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dababotu dib~apF xafiy~apF","text_ar":"دَبَبْتُ دِبَّةً خَفِيَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I crept along in a soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stealthy, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of creeping"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T, S.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dabiybN","text_ar":"دَبِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Anything that creeps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crawls, upon the earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and used as a coll. gen. n.]. (K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^akovara dib~apF h`*aA Albaladi","text_ar":"مَا اَكْثَرَ دِبَّةً هٰذَا البَلَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How many are the creeping,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crawling, things of this country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"town!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K"]}]}}